Preheat your #oven{} to 190°C/170°C fan/gas mark 5.

Halve, deseed and finely chop the @Apple{1%unit}.

In a #bowl{}, mix the @Vanilla Cake Batter{1%pouch}, @Ground Cinnamon{1%sachet} and chopped apple.

Line an #oven dish{} (approx 15x20cm) and pour the batter into it.

Scatter the @Biscuit Crumb{125%grams} over the top.

Place the cake mix into the #oven{} and bake until firm to touch and a #skewer{} inserted comes out clean, ~{45-50%minutes}.

Set aside to cool.

Drizzle over the @Salted Caramel{40%grams}.

Transfer the pear cake to a #plate{} or #serving board{}.

Slice and serve.

> Perfect for entertaining (or for when you fancy an afternoon treat), pear cake is equal parts soft, spongey and tasty - with a caramel biscuit top that's simply irresistible!